2023-05-17 12:20;cjplummer;Both of the failures so far have been with the new generational ZGC. I think I know why. JDK-8289765 fixed this type of issue by improving the filtered() method, which filters out ThreadStartEvents for threads we want to ignore:

    public static boolean filtered(Event event) {
        if (event instanceof ThreadStartEvent) {
            ThreadStartEvent tse = (ThreadStartEvent)event;
            String tname = tse.thread().name();
            String knownThreads[] = {
                "VM JFR Buffer Thread",
                "JFR request timer",
                "Reference Handler",
                "VirtualThread-unparker",
                "Common-Cleaner",
                "FinalizerThread",
                "ForkJoinPool"
            };
            for (String s : knownThreads) {
                if (tname.startsWith(s)) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }

Note that it filters "Common-Cleaner" and note that in the log we have:

# ERROR: debugger> ERROR: ThreadStartEvent is not for expected thread:  Cleaner-1

So it looks like generational ZGC has introduced a new thread name that we need to filter.;;;

